history.content: I would check BerkeleyTime past enrollment data for 16A vs 70 vs the Foreign Language class to decide which to Phase I.

It is a risk to prioritize a 1 unit class over major requirements. You can decide to take that risk but if it doesn't pan out (especially for 16A) it will likely be more difficult to find space in future semesters.

children.subject: <md>That makes sense; I'll definitely prioritize 16A for Phase 1. It seems that my foreign language class only fills up around Phase 2, so I'll phase 2 that class. Thanks for the input!</md>

history.content:
<md>I'll be an undeclared (intended CS) sophomore in L&S this Fall, and I was wondering if it's safe to use Phase 2 units for EECS 16A. I saw that there are 97 seats reserved for my category - how fast do these usually fill up? Should I use Phase 1 units on this class? 

I'm planning on taking a total of 14 units (16A + CS 70 + Foreign Language + 1-unit course), so if I have to Phase 1 16A, do I have a good chance of getting into CS 70 with Phase 2? 

Thanks! </md>
history.subject: Safe to Phase 2 EECS 16A?
